      <li class="ctsh clearfix" data-cid="38732768">
        <div class="ilst">
          <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/EG/"><img src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u1078604-121.jpg" alt="㦱峕胾𣥶夛" class="" /></a>
        </div>
        <div class="con">
          <div class="nlst">
            <h3>
              <div class="note-toggle rr">
                <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/38732768/" class="note-unfolder">展开</a>
                <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="note-folder">收起</a>
              </div>
              <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/38732768/" class="">第241页</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="clst">
            <p class="user"><a href="https://www.douban.com/people/EG/" class=" " title="㦱峕胾𣥶夛">㦱峕胾𣥶夛</a>
                (展开讲讲)
              
            </p>
            <div class="reading-note" data-cid="38732768">
              <div class="short">
                
                  <div class="ll">
                    <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/38732768/"><img src="https://img3.doubanio.com/view/page_note/small/public/p38732768-1.jpg"></a>
                  </div>
                  <span class="">翻译太差了……

（……存在于心中，也存在于现实中。）

我们权且说这是从拉丁文直接翻译的。那么，原文原教旨主义就在这里完败——这明显是不理解Anselm到底说了啥。
对比英文翻译：

Thus even the fool is convinced that something than which nothing
greater can be conceived is in the understanding, since when he hears
this, he understands it; and whatever is understood is in the understanding. And c...</span>
                  &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/38732768/">(<span class="">1回应</span>)</a>
                <p class="pl">
                  <span class="">2016-08-23 10:22</span>
                  
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="all hidden" style="display:none" >
                翻译太差了……
<div class="middle"><img src="https://img3.doubanio.com/view/page_note/large/public/p38732768-1.jpg" alt=""><br><span class="pic-title"></span></div>
（……存在于心中，也存在于现实中。）<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>我们权且说这是从拉丁文直接翻译的。那么，原文原教旨主义就在这里完败——这明显是不理解Anselm到底说了啥。<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>对比英文翻译：<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div><blockquote><q>Thus even the fool is convinced that something than which nothing
greater can be conceived is in the understanding, since when he hears
this, he understands it; and whatever is understood is in the understanding. And certainly that than which a greater cannot be conceived
cannot be in the understanding alone. For if it is . . . in the understanding alone, it can be conceived to exist in reality also, which is greater.
Thus if that than which a greater cannot be conceived is in the understanding alone, then that than which a greater cannot be conceived is
itself that than which a greater can be conceived. But surely this cannot
be. Thus without doubt something than which a greater cannot be conceived exists, both in the understanding and reality.</q></blockquote><div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>本书的中文翻译的问题（排名不分先后）：<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>1. 英译中，understanding、reality的表述是统一的，而中文一会儿是“心”，一会是“了解”，一会儿是“实际”，一会儿是“现实”……译名不统一，就完全丧失了Anselm那种表达分析命题的论证感。比较：“不管他了解的是什么，也都是在心中的” vs. “whatever is understood is in the understanding”。这完全就是外行和内行的差别。<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>2. 简直不可饶恕的是，something than which nothing greater can be conceived竟然理解成“可设想的无与伦比的伟大的东西”，that than which a greater connot be conceived竟然理解成“不可设想的无与伦比的伟大的东西”！这些明明就应该是“无与伦比的伟大的东西”或者“一个东西，比它更伟大的东西不可设想/没什么比它更伟大的东西可以设想”好吗……结果把“如果仅仅存在于理解中，那么无与伦比的伟大的东西本身就是‘有与伦比’的了”搞成了“那么，凡不可设想的无与伦比的伟大的东西，和可设想的无与伦比的伟大的东西，就是相同的了”这种笑话……<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>为什么觉得英译就一定对呢？因为道理说得通啊——所谓“内部拟测”。本体论论证怎么能搞出来“不可设想的无与伦比”“可设想的无与伦比”这种奇怪的东西……<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>这个故事告诉我们。看哲学书还是要看英文的，英语世界研究足够发达成熟——至少不能看中文的。
                  <div class="col-rec-con clearfix">
                    







